WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.060 --> 00:00:06.910
In the Game of Thrones TV show, Stannis Baratheon
dies with all the pathos and excitement of

00:00:06.910 --> 00:00:08.790
a damp fart.

00:00:08.790 --> 00:00:14.760
After a storyline four seasons long, he rolls
over and dies, and it’s the Starks who defeat

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:16.970
the Boltons and retake the north.

00:00:16.970 --> 00:00:23.869
But in the book series, northern politics
is an intricate web of alliances, rivalries,

00:00:23.869 --> 00:00:28.160
secrets and lies, while an apocalyptic winter
rises.

00:00:28.160 --> 00:00:35.050
And through the ice, Stannis marches on Winterfell,
with a plan to defeat the Boltons.

00:00:35.050 --> 00:00:39.640
The Boltons are holed up in Winterfell with
an army of Freys and northmen, most of whom

00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:45.100
secretly hate the Boltons . Wyman Manderly
“plots betrayal” , Barbrey Dustin stalks

00:00:45.100 --> 00:00:51.240
the crypts, and Theon is traumatised by Ramsay,
who calls Theon “Reek”.

00:00:51.240 --> 00:00:56.170
Ramsay doesn’t marry Sansa – he marries
a girl called Jeyne who the Boltons claim

00:00:56.170 --> 00:00:58.620
is Arya Stark.

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:03.410
Up on the Wall, Jon Snow tries to make peace
between the Night’s Watch and the wildlings,

00:01:03.410 --> 00:01:06.630
along with Melisandre, and Stannis’ family.

00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:12.999
Jon hears that his beloved sister Arya married
Ramsay , so he and Melisandre send the wildling

00:01:12.999 --> 00:01:16.270
king Mance Rayder to rescue her.

00:01:16.270 --> 00:01:21.240
Melisandre pretended to burn Mance, but that
was an illusion, and he’s actually still

00:01:21.240 --> 00:01:22.700
alive.

00:01:22.700 --> 00:01:27.850
So Mance and six wildling women infiltrate
Winterfell, and with their help, Jeyne and

00:01:27.850 --> 00:01:30.759
Theon escape to Stannis.

00:01:30.759 --> 00:01:34.350
Stannis and his army prepare to fight the
Boltons.

00:01:34.350 --> 00:01:39.249
But at the end of the latest book, Jon gets
a mysterious letter from Ramsay, called the

00:01:39.249 --> 00:01:40.600
Pink Letter.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:45.020
It says that Stannis is dead and Mance is
captured.

00:01:45.020 --> 00:01:50.680
Ramsay says he wants his bride back and wants
Theon back, he demands Stannis’ family,

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:56.859
and some wildlings – “Keep them from me”
he says, “and I will cut out your bastard’s

00:01:56.859 --> 00:02:02.700
heart and eat it” . So Jon is shook, and
he declares that he’ll leave the Night’s

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:09.379
Watch, and “ride south” to fight Ramsay
– so then the Watch stabs Jon to death.

00:02:09.379 --> 00:02:12.810
The Pink Letter changes everything in the
north.

00:02:12.810 --> 00:02:17.611
But fans suspect that it’s a trick or a
fake – Tormund warns us that the letter

00:02:17.611 --> 00:02:22.670
might be full of lies . So is Stannis really
dead?

00:02:22.670 --> 00:02:25.019
Was this letter even written by Ramsay?

00:02:25.019 --> 00:02:29.210
What’s happening at Winterfell in the Game
of Thrones books?

00:02:29.210 --> 00:02:34.620
It’s hard to believe that Stannis is dead
, cause his story’s not over yet.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:39.230
The whole fifth book builds up to his battle
for Winterfell , and author George Martin

00:02:39.230 --> 00:02:45.260
said we’ll see the battle in the next book
. So why would Stannis suddenly die off-screen

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:46.640
in this letter?

00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:50.110
Why spoil the climax of his story?

00:02:50.110 --> 00:02:55.900
Stannis is in a bad situation . His army is
“snowbound” and “starving” in a village

00:02:55.900 --> 00:02:57.290
near Winterfell.

00:02:57.290 --> 00:03:02.450
And the Boltons send the Freys out to attack
him . But Stannis is confident – he says

00:03:02.450 --> 00:03:07.990
“let them come”, and says he’ll turn
“the ground” to his “advantage” . What

00:03:07.990 --> 00:03:08.990
does he mean?

00:03:08.990 --> 00:03:14.210
At the start of the book, it says that Stannis
once went to an island with a lighthouse.

00:03:14.210 --> 00:03:18.569
He learned that sometimes, people would turn
off the lighthouse and create a false light

00:03:18.569 --> 00:03:25.650
somewhere else to lure ships into danger . And
now, it just so happens that Stannis’ camp

00:03:25.650 --> 00:03:31.079
has a watchtower with a “beacon fire”
that burns day and night . And next to the

00:03:31.079 --> 00:03:37.030
camp are some frozen lakes . His men fish
the lakes, by cutting holes in the ice, and

00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:42.629
the ice becomes so dangerous that some men
fall through into the water . So if Stannis

00:03:42.629 --> 00:03:48.150
puts out the fire on his watchtower, and he
lights a false beacon on the frozen lake,

00:03:48.150 --> 00:03:53.340
he could lure the Freys onto the dangerous
ice, and attack them there – maybe break

00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:57.580
the ice with catapults so that the Freys fall
through and drown.

00:03:57.580 --> 00:04:03.319
That must be what Stannis means by turning
“the ground” to his “advantage” . So

00:04:03.319 --> 00:04:08.510
the hints are all there –it seems almost
certain that Stannis will use a false fire

00:04:08.510 --> 00:04:11.019
on the lakes to defeat the Freys.

00:04:11.019 --> 00:04:14.920
You can read more about this theory in the
articles below.

00:04:14.920 --> 00:04:20.180
But if Stannis wins this battle, why does
the Pink Letter say Stannis is dead?

00:04:20.180 --> 00:04:25.680
Well last time we see him, Stannis specifically
says “you may hear that I am dead” , so

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:29.130
some fans think he’s planning to fake his
own death.

00:04:29.130 --> 00:04:33.260
Cause as well as the Freys, the Manderlys
are coming for Stannis.

00:04:33.260 --> 00:04:36.870
But the Manderlys are coming “separately”
from the Freys , cause they’ve been fighting

00:04:36.870 --> 00:04:42.080
– at one point, Wyman serves meat pies made
out of Freys.

00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:48.180
Wyman is planning to betray the Boltons – and
he made a secret deal to support Stannis . So

00:04:48.180 --> 00:04:53.139
instead of fighting each other, maybe Stannis
and the Manderlys will work together – and

00:04:53.139 --> 00:04:56.880
will trick the Boltons into thinking that
Stannis is dead.

00:04:56.880 --> 00:05:02.220
So like, after Stannis beats the Freys, Wyman
could go back to Winterfell and tell the Boltons

00:05:02.220 --> 00:05:07.360
that Stannis was defeated – as proof, Manderly
could have Stannis’ sword Lightbringer,

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:10.169
which Ramsay says he has in the Pink Letter.

00:05:10.169 --> 00:05:15.360
But secretly, Stannis would be still alive
– he could use the low visibility in the

00:05:15.360 --> 00:05:21.330
snowstorm to sneak up for an attack on Winterfell
. And Ramsay would be totally unprepared,

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:22.740
thinking Stannis is dead.

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:27.449
He’d just be angry that Jon sent Mance to
steal his bride.

00:05:27.449 --> 00:05:33.110
That’s why Ramsay threatens Jon in the Letter,
and demands Jeyne and Theon, who would likely

00:05:33.110 --> 00:05:35.800
seek refuge with Jon at the Wall.

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:41.170
So this is a pretty likely explanation of
the Pink Letter – Ramsay wrote the letter,

00:05:41.170 --> 00:05:45.840
thinking that Stannis is dead, though Stannis
is actually still alive.

00:05:45.840 --> 00:05:48.260
But there are other theories.

00:05:48.260 --> 00:05:54.550
The letter seems to fit Ramsay’s personality
– it’s angry and cruel . Ramsay repeatedly

00:05:54.550 --> 00:06:00.340
calls Jon “bastard” – cause Ramsay is
insecure about being a bastard himself . Ramsay

00:06:00.340 --> 00:06:05.240
is also “cunning” and manipulative – he
might be trying to provoke Jon into doing

00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:06.960
something stupid.

00:06:06.960 --> 00:06:11.370
But some details of the letter seem off.

00:06:11.370 --> 00:06:14.699
In the book, we see three threatening letters
from Ramsay.

00:06:14.699 --> 00:06:20.470
Asha Greyjoy gets a letter, Jon gets a letter,
and then Jon gets the Pink Letter.

00:06:20.470 --> 00:06:22.919
And these letters are described in detail.

00:06:22.919 --> 00:06:28.699
Asha’s letter is “tightly rolled and sealed
with a button of hard pink wax” . It’s

00:06:28.699 --> 00:06:32.140
written in “blood” , that looks like “brown”
ink.

00:06:32.140 --> 00:06:37.050
The handwriting is “huge” and “spiky”
. It’s signed by Ramsay, and by his allies

00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:41.100
Lady Dustin, Cerwyn, four Ryswells, and one
Umber.

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:46.039
The second letter, to Jon, is described almost
exactly the same way.

00:06:46.039 --> 00:06:50.669
“tightly rolled and sealed, with a button
of hard pink wax” , blood-brown ink, huge

00:06:50.669 --> 00:06:55.500
spiky hand, signed by Ramsay, Dustin, Cerwyn,
Ryswells and Umber.

00:06:55.500 --> 00:07:01.900
It’s all super specific and consistent,
so it’s weird that the Pink Letter is described

00:07:01.900 --> 00:07:02.900
differently.

00:07:02.900 --> 00:07:08.159
It’s got a “smear” of pink wax, but
there’s no mention of brown ink, or a huge

00:07:08.159 --> 00:07:09.409
spiky hand.

00:07:09.409 --> 00:07:13.560
It’s signed by Ramsay, but not by anyone
else.

00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:16.620
Why is the Pink Letter different?

00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:19.819
Some of the content of the letter is also
suspicious.

00:07:19.819 --> 00:07:25.120
Like, it makes sense that Ramsay wants his
“bride” Jeyne, and his “Reek” Theon.

00:07:25.120 --> 00:07:28.890
And it makes sense that he wants Stannis’
family as political prisoners.

00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:35.069
But Ramsay also says he wants the “wildling
princess” Val, and her baby nephew . Why

00:07:35.069 --> 00:07:37.300
would he want these wildlings?

00:07:37.300 --> 00:07:41.710
How does Ramsay even know that Val’s baby
nephew exists?

00:07:41.710 --> 00:07:46.069
If Ramsay really did capture Mance, he could’ve
interrogated him to learn these details.

00:07:46.069 --> 00:07:48.530
But it’s not clear why he would care.

00:07:48.530 --> 00:07:53.190
So it’s surprising that so much of this
letter is focussed on Mance and the wildlings

00:07:53.190 --> 00:07:57.539
– is he just that angry at Mance for rescuing
Jeyne?

00:07:57.539 --> 00:08:02.510
The letter refers to the Night’s Watch as
“black crows” , a term that’s almost

00:08:02.510 --> 00:08:04.599
only used by wildlings.

00:08:04.599 --> 00:08:10.210
The letter talks about heads on walls, and
threatens to cut out Jon’s heart, when Ramsay’s

00:08:10.210 --> 00:08:13.080
favourite kind of execution is flaying.

00:08:13.080 --> 00:08:18.879
But there is another character who once threatened
to cut out Jon’s heart – a wildling who

00:08:18.879 --> 00:08:24.020
would care about Val and the baby, the only
character mentioned by name in this letter

00:08:24.020 --> 00:08:30.330
– Mance Rayder, the wildling king . Maybe
the reason why the Pink Letter is different

00:08:30.330 --> 00:08:34.640
to Ramsay’s other letters, and the reason
why it’s so focussed on wildlings, is that

00:08:34.640 --> 00:08:38.810
Ramsay didn’t write it – Mance did.

00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:45.170
In the books, Mance Rayder is a maverick charismatic
leader, who uses “cunning” and deception

00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:47.120
to manipulate people.

00:08:47.120 --> 00:08:52.339
Right of the start of Book 1, when King Robert
visits Winterfell, Mance is actually at that

00:08:52.339 --> 00:08:56.839
feast – he climbs the Wall, and comes in
disguise to spy.

00:08:56.839 --> 00:09:02.120
In Book 3, Mance claims that he has the Horn
of Winter , a magic Horn with the power to

00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:08.800
destroy the Wall – but it turns out, Mance
lied to manipulate Jon . Mance has history

00:09:08.800 --> 00:09:14.110
with Jon – the first time they met, Mance
warned Jon not to play tricks with him – but

00:09:14.110 --> 00:09:17.610
Jon ends up betraying Mance by leaving the
wildlings.

00:09:17.610 --> 00:09:22.180
So maybe Mance pulls a trick on Jon by writing
the Pink Letter.

00:09:22.180 --> 00:09:26.390
Mance has recently used a lot of the same
language that’s in the Pink Letter – he

00:09:26.390 --> 00:09:31.410
calls Melisandre a “red witch”, calls
Jon “bastard” , and calls the Night’s

00:09:31.410 --> 00:09:36.900
Watch “crows” . He says that Mance was
burned “for all the world to see” , and

00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:43.240
the Pink Letter says Mance is in a cage “for
all the north to see” . It’s probably

00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:48.470
possible for Mance to fake a letter from Ramsay
– when Mance infiltrates Winterfell, he

00:09:48.470 --> 00:09:53.100
pretends to be a singer called “Abel”,
and he hangs around the Boltons , so he mighta

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:57.360
learned enough about Ramsay’s character
to impersonate him in a letter.

00:09:57.360 --> 00:10:02.020
Mance speaks with Theon, so he coulda learned
about Ramsay’s relationship with “Reek”

00:10:02.020 --> 00:10:03.510
and with Jeyne.

00:10:03.510 --> 00:10:08.740
And he maybe could’ve stolen some pink wax
and a raven to send the Letter – he woulda

00:10:08.740 --> 00:10:14.019
been in a rush, so maybe that’s why the
letter’s sealed with a “smear” of wax.

00:10:14.019 --> 00:10:18.209
The difficult question is why Mance would
write the Letter?

00:10:18.209 --> 00:10:22.860
Like, even if Mance could predict that the
Letter would make Jon ride south with some

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:26.130
wildlings, how does that help Mance?

00:10:26.130 --> 00:10:30.730
Mance doesn’t want the wildlings to fight
in Stannis’ war – Mance says his “people

00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:36.010
have bled enough” . Maybe Mance wants help
to escape Winterfell.

00:10:36.010 --> 00:10:40.670
But if Mance wants help, there’s gotta be
a better way to ask for it than to impersonate

00:10:40.670 --> 00:10:47.000
Ramsay to provoke Jon into rallying wildlings,
it’s a ridiculously convoluted plan.

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:49.070
Why would Mance ask for “Reek”?

00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:55.940
And why ask for Val and the baby, his baby
– that could only put them in danger, right?

00:10:55.940 --> 00:11:01.540
Mance does seem to have some secret plan in
Winterfell – he investigates the Winterfell

00:11:01.540 --> 00:11:07.490
crypts . And the name Abel is anagram of Bael,
a legendary wildling said to have snuck into

00:11:07.490 --> 00:11:12.589
Winterfell and stolen a Stark girl – just
like Mance sneaks into Winterfell to rescue

00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:18.170
Arya Stark . Bael is said to have hidden in
the Winterfell crypts – so maybe Mance’s

00:11:18.170 --> 00:11:20.550
plan is to hide in the crypts.

00:11:20.550 --> 00:11:25.450
Maybe he’s searching for the real Horn of
Winter there – he searched for the horn

00:11:25.450 --> 00:11:31.320
in “graves” beyond the Wall – maybe
now he’s searching for it in Stark graves.

00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:34.100
So Mance is up to something.

00:11:34.100 --> 00:11:37.550
And there are connections between Mance and
the letter.

00:11:37.550 --> 00:11:42.070
But it’s hard to see why Mance would write
the Letter.

00:11:42.070 --> 00:11:45.060
Another theory is that Stannis wrote the Pink
Letter.

00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:50.230
Cause in his last chapter, Stannis is facing
a battle he might not win.

00:11:50.230 --> 00:11:55.019
Even if he beats the Freys with a beacon and
the lakes, there are still thousands of Boltons

00:11:55.019 --> 00:11:57.560
in one of the strongest castles in Westeros.

00:11:57.560 --> 00:12:04.090
Stannis’ army might not be enough – so
maybe he wants the help of Jon and the wildlings.

00:12:04.090 --> 00:12:08.610
Stannis has asked for Jon’s support before,
but Jon said he's sworn to the Night's Watch

00:12:08.610 --> 00:12:11.800
. Asking directly doesn’t work.

00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:16.830
But if Stannis fakes a letter from Ramsay,
threatening Jon and his sister, and threatening

00:12:16.830 --> 00:12:18.730
the wildling king Mance…

00:12:18.730 --> 00:12:24.490
That could motivate Jon and the wildlings
to ride south and help Stannis win his war.

00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:29.270
This could also fit with Stannis’ plan to
make Jon Lord of Winterfell – if he leaves

00:12:29.270 --> 00:12:32.370
the Watch, he might as well take up Stannis’
offer.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:37.680
And thing is, Stannis just captured a Bolton
maester , who would know Ramsay’s writing

00:12:37.680 --> 00:12:41.880
style, and might have the wax and raven to
send the Pink Letter.

00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:46.709
Stannis also captured Theon, who could tell
him about Mance and Reek and other details

00:12:46.709 --> 00:12:47.830
in the letter.

00:12:47.830 --> 00:12:51.790
So it seems possible for Stannis to write
the Pink Letter.

00:12:51.790 --> 00:12:55.110
And unlike Mance, Stannis has a clear motive.

00:12:55.110 --> 00:13:00.360
But the biggest problem with this is that
Stannis' army is starving, it’s so bad they’re

00:13:00.360 --> 00:13:05.550
starting to eat their own dead – so Stannis
doesn't have time to wait around for Jon and

00:13:05.550 --> 00:13:08.149
an army to travel down from the Wall.

00:13:08.149 --> 00:13:13.350
That distance would take weeks or months to
cover in winter, by which time Stannis and

00:13:13.350 --> 00:13:18.510
his army would be dead . It might work if
Stannis sent the Letter earlier, but earlier

00:13:18.510 --> 00:13:23.990
he didn’t have Theon and the maester, so
he wouldn’t know about Mance and Reek and

00:13:23.990 --> 00:13:25.449
the stuff in the letter.

00:13:25.449 --> 00:13:29.000
Also, faking a letter just isn’t Stannis’
style.

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:33.490
Like, it’s one thing to pull off a military
maneuver with a false beacon.

00:13:33.490 --> 00:13:39.970
But faking the Pink Letter means impersonating
Ramsay, and emotionally manipulating Jon – Stannis

00:13:39.970 --> 00:13:45.209
is terrible with emotions, he’s bad with
people , and psychologically manipulating

00:13:45.209 --> 00:13:49.320
Jon with a fake letter just isn’t the sort
of thing he’d do.

00:13:49.320 --> 00:13:54.220
Further, if the real purpose of the Pink Letter
is to motivate Jon to come south, you’d

00:13:54.220 --> 00:13:59.649
think it’d talk more about Arya, and less
about hostages and Mance.

00:13:59.649 --> 00:14:04.800
Why would Stannis demand “Reek”, when
Stannis already has “Reek”, and Jon doesn’t

00:14:04.800 --> 00:14:07.199
know what a “Reek” is?

00:14:07.199 --> 00:14:10.560
Stannis probably didn’t write the Pink Letter.

00:14:10.560 --> 00:14:13.810
Some fans argue that Melisandre wrote the
Letter.

00:14:13.810 --> 00:14:20.130
Mel does have secret schemes happening – she
faked Mance's death, and sending him to Winterfell

00:14:20.130 --> 00:14:21.820
was her idea.

00:14:21.820 --> 00:14:28.009
Jon suspects that Mel has some other secret
plan with Mance . So some fans think that

00:14:28.009 --> 00:14:34.190
Mance and Melisandre wrote the Letter together
– though the motive is still unclear.

00:14:34.190 --> 00:14:39.089
Melisandre has visions of the future in her
fires, and she actually predicts the arrival

00:14:39.089 --> 00:14:44.750
of the Pink Letter before it comes . So maybe
she also knew what would happen after the

00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:50.480
Pink Letter came – that Jon would be stabbed
to death, but then be resurrected by Mel’s

00:14:50.480 --> 00:14:55.050
magic, that would ultimately help save the
world.

00:14:55.050 --> 00:15:00.459
Maybe Mel finally realised that Stannis isn’t
the chosen one – Jon is , so she could’ve

00:15:00.459 --> 00:15:05.580
written the Pink Letter to get Jon killed
to fulfil his destiny.

00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:11.600
But Melisandre repeatedly warns Jon not to
get stabbed , and last we saw, she still thinks

00:15:11.600 --> 00:15:17.639
Stannis is the chosen one . So there’s no
real evidence for Melisandre writing the Pink

00:15:17.639 --> 00:15:19.300
Letter.

00:15:19.300 --> 00:15:21.640
Another possibility is Barbrey Dustin.

00:15:21.640 --> 00:15:25.699
She’s a new character in Book 5, and she’s
mysterious.

00:15:25.699 --> 00:15:30.660
Openly, she supports the Boltons, but she
hates Ramsay , because Ramsay murdered her

00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:36.889
nephew . Barbrey asks Theon to show her the
Winterfell crypts , around the time Mance

00:15:36.889 --> 00:15:42.490
asks about the crypts – so some fans think
Mance and Barbrey might be working together.

00:15:42.490 --> 00:15:47.779
There’re also hints of Barbrey working with
Wyman Manderly and his conspiracy – like

00:15:47.779 --> 00:15:53.209
maybe they wrote the Pink Letter to lure Jon
south so he can be King in the North – go

00:15:53.209 --> 00:15:56.399
watch our Grand Northern Conspiracy video.

00:15:56.399 --> 00:16:01.730
So there’s a lot of intrigue and mystery
happening in the north – it seems like every

00:16:01.730 --> 00:16:07.620
second character has some secret plot or identity
– even this bloody baby is actually secretly

00:16:07.620 --> 00:16:11.800
a different baby, because Jon swapped him
with Gilly’s baby.

00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:15.360
But most of this stuff is probably unrelated
to the Pink Letter.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:19.509
The Pink Letter is memorable cause it’s
the last thing that happens before Jon dies.

00:16:19.509 --> 00:16:25.449
And it’s been nine years since that book
came out, so fans have had a lot of time to

00:16:25.449 --> 00:16:29.570
overthink it and come up with crazy theories
about who wrote the Letter.

00:16:29.570 --> 00:16:34.149
The theories are fun, but based on the text,
it the makes the most sense for Ramsay to

00:16:34.149 --> 00:16:35.149
write the Letter.

00:16:35.149 --> 00:16:40.829
Cause the Letter doesn’t just have a plot
purpose of provoking Jon and getting him stabbed.

00:16:40.829 --> 00:16:46.170
It has an emotional purpose by forcing Jon
to choose between family and duty, and setting

00:16:46.170 --> 00:16:48.720
up Ramsay as a hated enemy.

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:53.509
If it turns out that the Pink Letter was a
fake for some obscure subplot, that could

00:16:53.509 --> 00:16:58.279
take away from the emotional weight of this
gut-punch at the end of the book.

00:16:58.279 --> 00:17:03.480
And there can still be a twist to the Pink
Letter – that Stannis isn’t really dead,

00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:08.410
cause there actually are strong hints in the
text that Stannis will beat the Freys.

00:17:08.410 --> 00:17:13.870
But we’ll only know the truth when the next
book comes out – until then, all we’ve

00:17:13.870 --> 00:17:16.420
got is theories.

00:17:16.420 --> 00:17:20.140
If you wanna know more about the mysteries
of Game of Thrones, you’ve gotta check out

00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:21.140
the books.

00:17:21.140 --> 00:17:24.850
As well as the main series, there’s the
worldbook, and Fire and Blood, and the Dunk

00:17:24.850 --> 00:17:29.790
and Egg stories, and you can get any one of
